T1 — FL-01: Family + Type data model

  ▎ git checkout -b fl-01-data-model

  You are working in a BIM (architectural CAD) web app monorepo. Two files to touch:
    packages/core/src/index.ts          ← extend existing element types
    packages/web/src/families/types.ts  ← new file to create

  CONTEXT — CURRENT STATE
  =======================
  In packages/core/src/index.ts, the `family_type` element today is:
    {
      kind: 'family_type';
      id: string;
      discipline: 'door' | 'window' | 'generic';
      parameters: Record<string, unknown>;
    }

  Door and window elements have `familyTypeId?: string | null` already.
  Stair and railing elements do not have `overrideParams`.

  TASK — packages/core/src/index.ts
  ==================================
  1. Add a FamilyDiscipline type alias above or near the family_type element
     kind (keep it co-located so readers find it easily):
       export type FamilyDiscipline =
         | 'door' | 'window' | 'stair' | 'railing'
         | 'wall_type' | 'floor_type' | 'roof_type'
         | 'column' | 'beam'
         | 'generic';

  2. Extend the `family_type` element kind to:
       {
         kind: 'family_type';
         id: string;
         name: string;               // "Single Flush : 900×2100"
         familyId: string;           // e.g. 'door.single-flush'
         discipline: FamilyDiscipline;
         parameters: Record<string, unknown>;
         isBuiltIn?: boolean;        // true = ships with app
       }

  3. Add `overrideParams?: Record<string, unknown>` to the door, window,
     stair, and railing element kinds. (Check each kind's shape and add the
     optional field; do not change any existing fields.)

  TASK — packages/web/src/families/types.ts (CREATE NEW FILE)
  ============================================================
  Create the file. It should export these interfaces (used by both the
  catalog and the renderer — no Three.js imports, pure types):

    import type { FamilyDiscipline } from '@bim-ai/core';

    export interface FamilyParamDef {
      key:      string;
      label:    string;
      type:     'length_mm' | 'angle_deg' | 'material_key' | 'boolean' | 'option';
      default:  unknown;
      options?: string[];       // for 'option' type
      min?:     number;
      max?:     number;
      instanceOverridable: boolean;
    }

    export interface FamilyDefinition {
      id:           string;   // e.g. 'door.single-flush'
      name:         string;   // "Single Flush Door"
      discipline:   FamilyDiscipline;
      thumbnail?:   string;   // base64 PNG or URL, generated lazily
      params:       FamilyParamDef[];
      defaultTypes: {
        name:       string;
        familyId:   string;
        discipline: FamilyDiscipline;
        parameters: Record<string, unknown>;
        isBuiltIn:  true;
      }[];
    }

    // Parameter resolution: instance override > type params > family default > inline fallback
    export function resolveParam(
      key: string,
      instanceOverrides: Record<string, unknown> | undefined,
      typeParameters: Record<string, unknown> | undefined,
      familyDef: FamilyDefinition | undefined,
      inlineFallback: unknown,
    ): unknown {
      return (
        instanceOverrides?.[key] ??
        typeParameters?.[key] ??
        familyDef?.params.find(p => p.key === key)?.default ??
        inlineFallback
      );
    }

  VERIFY
  ======
    pnpm --filter core typecheck   (if available) or
    pnpm --filter web typecheck
    pnpm --filter web test run

  No new tests are required beyond typecheck passing. If there is a test file
  for core types, add a smoke-test that FamilyDiscipline includes 'railing'.

